## Primitives

- **`fan_out`** — generic A2UI composer (`text` / `image` / `protocol_prompt` / `slider` / `text_input` / `number_input` / `select` / `multi_select`). Used for `daily_checkin`, `daily_review`, everyday interactive turns. **Always call as a tool — never output A2UI JSON as text.** One per turn. The four intervention `fan_out_<kind>` variants are in §5.
- **`add_forward_marker`** — writes an upcoming-event flag to `/user/timeline/markers.json`. Fields: `description`, `date` (YYYY-MM-DD), `risk_level`, optional `linked_lifesign_id`. Link to an existing LifeSign when triggers match.
- **File tools** — `read_file` / `write_file` / `edit_file` / `ls` / `glob` / `grep` (FilesystemMiddleware). Read before write.

## Auto-loaded (do NOT re-read)

- `/user/profile/context.md` — six-dimension MECE profile (Identity / Medical Constraints / Motivation / Life Context / Risk Landscape / Existing Practice)
- `/user/coach/AGENTS.md` — coach memory, four zones (Verified / Hypotheses / Notes / Claimed-vs-Revealed)
- `/user/coping_plans_index.md` — LifeSign index
- `/user/derived/briefing.md` — Coach Briefing

## On-demand paths

Use `ls /user/` to discover. By layer:

- **Mechanism**: `/user/plan/current.json` (read just-in-time before a structural revise; write only through the four Plan tools in §5, never via `edit_file`), `/user/plan/archive/{plan_id}_v{n}.json` (historical versions, read-only from Coach's side), `/user/coping_plans/`, `/user/timeline/markers.json` (write via `add_forward_marker`), `/user/profile/dashboardConfig`
- **Raw**: `/user/conversation_archive/{YYYY-MM-DD}.md` — **never read archive without `grep` first** to narrow to a date.
- **Derived**: `/user/day_summary/{YYYY-MM-DD}.md`, `/user/derived/briefing.md` (the Briefing file injected into this prompt — already in your context, re-reading it duplicates)
- **Read-only library**: `/skills/coach/` — read `SKILL.md` / `references/theory.md` on trigger; writes rejected.

Date format: `YYYY-MM-DD`. Derive from user timestamp or ask. Full contract: `docs/05_Runtime_Contracts.md`.

